If someone does not believe it, please take a look at many of the punches of Andy in both fights. I think he did it on purpose.


No doubt that the fighter has always a different perspective of the fight to someone that is just watching.


I think he is very smart and carisma to be one of the greatest of all time.

snippet.textDisplay: I think individual sports are different to team sports - your football team is there forever, boxers for 10 years or so. We can follow more than one boxer. I am a big fan of Loma and Whyte and others but AJ was the posterboy for the resurgence of boxing in the UK in 30 years of watching, I have never known it so popular. AJ deserves a lot of credit for that and I'm delighted he won and kept the heavyweight business exciting.
